modules.description: Creates and manages a parallel processing environment that executes tasks across multiple workers, handling request-response cycles with Lwt for asynchronous operations. It operates on custom types representing service requests, responses, and environment data, enabling controlled task distribution and result aggregation. Used to process streams of data in parallel, submit individual tasks for execution, and cleanly shut down worker pools.

Provides functions to retrieve the number of available CPU cores and check if hyper-threading is enabled. Operates on system-specific data structures and platform-dependent values. Used to optimize parallel task scheduling and resource allocation in concurrent applications.

Manages parallel task execution across worker pools using Lwt, processing custom request and response types to distribute work and collect results. Supports streaming data processing, individual task submission, and graceful shutdown of worker environments. Operations include task dispatch, result aggregation, and environment management. Examples include parallel image processing, batch job execution, and real-time data analysis.
